\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs28 \b HUMAN LAMINAR FLOW: THE TEMPORAL NULL STATE \b0\fs24\par
\par
\b 1. DEFINITION OF FLOW \b0\par
In fluid systems, laminar flow represents a state of minimum turbulence and maximum efficiency. In human neurobiology, this manifests as a complete loss of the sense of time. This "temporal null state" is the primary indicator of successful auditory entrainment.\par
\par
\b 2. REDUCING PSYCHOLOGICAL FRICTION \b0\par
Auditory interventions (Music as Medicine) function as a smoothing agent. By providing a consistent, resonant signal, we can transition a "turbulent" nervous system into a "laminar" state, where the cognitive load of self-monitoring is eliminated.\par
\par
\b 3. TIME AS TURBULENCE \b0\par
The perception of time is often a byproduct of internal friction. By achieving a high-fidelity connection with a musical or vocal "Continuum," the listener enters a state of lossless information processing?the sense of time disappears because the "noise" of tracking it has been removed.\par
\par
\i "Laminar flow is the physical expression of a mind in harmony with the Continuum."\i0\par
